00:14:57,963 --> 00:15:00,064
to place that on the screen.

267
00:15:00,064 --> 00:15:01,984
So you wanted to reduce any clutter that

268
00:15:01,984 --> 00:15:07,445
could be where the player is cutting or looking at the ship.

269
00:15:07,945 --> 00:15:12,747
And we wanted to keep those core pieces of UI bits of information,

270
00:15:12,747 --> 00:15:15,869
so your tool info, object info, talking heads,

271
00:15:15,869 --> 00:15:20,050
and your stats close to that center, so close to the bottom center,

272
00:15:20,050 --> 00:15:22,891
reducing the cognitive load for the player.

273
00:15:22,891 --> 00:15:26,593
It's the central cutting zone, if you will,

