329
00:18:58,056 --> 00:19:01,098
We were heavily inspired by fighter pilot jets,

330
00:19:01,098 --> 00:19:07,082
and we wanted to use those as an example to build a sense of expertise,

331
00:19:07,082 --> 00:19:09,043
that when a fighter pilot looks at this,

332
00:19:09,043 --> 00:19:11,625
they know what they're looking at, but a layman wouldn't.

333
00:19:11,625 --> 00:19:15,808
So how do we condense information, tell the player that they're an expert,

334
00:19:15,808 --> 00:19:18,910
but also explain it to them in case they ever get lost?

335
00:19:19,410 --> 00:19:24,313
So we tried to build that emotion of an expert,

336
00:19:24,313 --> 00:19:27,275
of the fact that this is displayed onto your helmet,

337
00:19:27,275 --> 00:19:32,498
through the effects in the game.

338
00:19:32,498 --> 00:19:35,340
So, I'll give you an example here.

