00:22:58,945 --> 00:23:01,265
work report akin to the contract screen

394
00:23:01,265 --> 00:23:02,265
that you saw before.

395
00:23:02,809 --> 00:23:09,396
to tell the player how they died, what they can do to improve this gameplay,

396
00:23:09,396 --> 00:23:16,203
and we've kept the funny quip and the finger stamp because your identity is kind of tied to that.

397
00:23:18,220 --> 00:23:25,763
This not only paved the way for a more interesting death experience that added no more than 10

398
00:23:25,763 --> 00:23:30,125
seconds to the gameplay and got the player back into the game as soon as they finished,

399
00:23:30,125 --> 00:23:36,267
but it influenced the onboarding experience which is something that kind of came in last minute

400
00:23:36,267 --> 00:23:40,188
because the death experience already existed where what you see now,

